# Check every text file out with LF, on every platform.
#
# Without this, a Windows working tree gets CRLF while the repository (and CI)
# hold LF. `prettier --check .` then fails locally on files that are perfectly
# clean in git — so its output becomes noise you learn to ignore, and a genuine
# violation hides in the middle of it. That is exactly how a stray blank line in
# JoinRoomScreen.tsx reached main and broke CI four commits running.
#
# The repository content does not change: it was already LF. Only the checkout does.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets must never be touched.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.webp binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf binary
*.otf binary
*.mp3 binary
*.wav binary
